Got you, bro! Let's strip out MoneroOcean and configure this strictly for unMineable, targeting Shiba Inu (SHIB) on the Binance Smart Chain (BEP-20).⚠️ How unMineable Network Payouts WorkBecause unMineable features multi-chain support, your wallet address syntax in the config.json text block always begins with the prefix SHIB:.Your physical wallet address string looks the exact same across Ethereum (ERC-20) and Binance Smart Chain (BEP-20). To tell unMineable you specifically want a BEP-20 transfer, you just run this configuration file, then log onto the unMineable Website, type your address into the search box, and click Switch Network to select BSC (BEP-20).Here is your exact, ultra-clean single-pool JSON setup. Copy and paste this directly over your current config.json file:json{
    "autosave": true,
    "donate-level": 1,
    "cpu": {
        "enabled": true,
        "max-threads-hint": 75,
        "priority": 0
    },
    "api": {
        "id": "hawk",
        "worker-id": "hawk-miner",
        "http": {
            "enabled": true,
            "host": "127.0.0.1",
            "port": 60606,
            "access-token": null,
            "restricted": false
        }
    },
    "pools": [
        {
            "algo": "rx/0",
            "url": "stratum+tcp://rx.unmineable.com:3333",
            "user": "SHIB:YOUR_BEP20_SHIBA_INU_WALLET_ADDRESS.hawk-miner",
            "pass": "x",
            "keepalive": true,
            "tls": false
        }
    ]
}
Use code with caution.🛠️ Quick Steps to Make It Live:YOUR_BEP20_SHIBA_INU_WALLET_ADDRESS: Replace this text inside the quotation marks with your actual Shiba Inu public deposit address string (usually starts with 0x). Make sure you leave SHIB: right before it and .hawk-miner right after it.max-threads-hint: Set to 75 (75% CPU load). Do not change it back to the plain text word threads or XMRig will break.
